[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/new_minor_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{With 13 points and 4 cards in each minor suit you should open 1\D. Partner responds 1\S.  

You have a minimum, balanced hand. It would not be wrong to say 2\C, but 1NT is probably better. Partner says 2\C.  

Do not support the \Cs if you have another decent bid. This is New Minor Forcing and partner may or may not have a \C suit. You do not have 3 \Ss. You do not have a 4-card \H suit. You do have a \H stopper, so bid 2NT. Partner then bids 3NT.}

